{"questionId":"17826","questionHtml":"<p>A cell of electromotive force (emf) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi></math> and zero internal resistance is in the circuit shown.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/c28c60bd5204c353650bc749cb8c5704ac60be72.png\" width=\"361\" height=\"413\"></p>\n<p>What is correct for loop WXYUW?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>R</mi></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>R</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>R</mi></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>R</mi></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"17826","referenceCode":"20N.1.HL.TZ0.15","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A cell of electromotive force (emf) E and zero internal resistance is in the circuit shown. What is correct for loop WXYUW? A. E=3I1R-I3R B. E=I3R-I2R C. E=I3R D. E=2I2R-I3R","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"15","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.2 – Heating effect of electric currents","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}